      <section eId="sec_10_3_2">
        <num>10-3-2</num>
        <content>
          <p>In all cases the endorser may be sued in the same action and in the same county with the maker or drawer or acceptor.</p>
          <p>(Laws 1826, Cobb's 1851 Digest, p. 594; Code 1863, § 2732; Code 1868, § 2740; Code 1873, § 2782; Code 1882, § 2782; Civil Code 1895, § 3691; Civil Code 1910, § 4283; Code 1933, § 14-1803.)</p>
